<p>GDP growth: 2.2% GDP: $540bn (PPP: $976bn) Inflation: 16.5% Population: 76.8m GDP per head: $7,040 (PPP: $12,720)</p>

<p>Opponents of President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad will use the 2012 parliamentary elections to reclaim powers for the legislature, and preparations will gather speed for his replacement in the 2013 presidential contest. Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the supreme leader, will stick by his fractious president at a high cost to his own authority. International sanctions, fragmented government and clerical meddling will crimp the economy.</p>

<p>To watch: Iran rising. Although official protests are sharply limited by the regime, a popular uprising inspired by the Arab spring is a distinct possibility.</p>

